trend_summary: Built-up clusters expand steadily west-to-east, filling in along the main highway and pushing into former woodland and cropland. New residential subdivisions and some light industrial roofs appear, while scattered clearings enlarge. Despite growth, most of the corridor remains green, keeping overall settlement loose.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of housing estates around the central highway junction.
Emergence of several cul-de-sac subdivision grids in the eastern half.
Noticeable increase in light-colored industrial/commercial roofs near the western core.
Forest patches converted to open ground or pasture, especially south of the spine road.
Minor widening/straightening of arterial roads and addition of new connector segments.
